Subpackage in Java:

1. Package inside the package is called subpackage. It should be created as categorize the package further.

Example: Sun Microsystem has defined a package named java that conatains many classes like System, String, Reader, Writer, Socket etc..
These classes represent particular groups. 

2. There can be only one public class in java source file and it must be saved by class name. 

Example:

class A{
}
class B{
}
public class C{
}

Save the file as C.java otherwise compiler will give error.

3. How to put two public classes in one one package

package point;

public class A{
}

package point;

public class B{
}